scenario:
No violation can be determined from the call site: the statement digest_update_with_colon(da); itself does not call any <string.h> function and therefore does not by itself violate MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17. To decide definitively you must inspect the implementation of digest_update_with_colon. A concrete violation scenario would be, for example, if digest_update_with_colon were implemented as:

void digest_update_with_colon(struct DigestAlgorithm *da) {
  char colon[1];
  strcpy(colon, ":"); /* strcpy writes two bytes (':' + '\0') into a 1-byte buffer -> buffer overflow */
  digest_update(da, colon, strlen(colon));
}

which would use <string.h> functions and write beyond the bounds of colon, violating Rule 21.17.
